a+b\equiv0\pmod m
c+d\equiv 0\pmod m
ac\equiv bd\pmod m
$$ I tried 
a\equiv -b,c\equiv-d\pmod m
ac\equiv (-b)(-d)\pmod m\equiv bd
ac+bc=mk
bc+bd=mj
a+b\equiv0\pmod m\Longrightarrow m\mid a+b\Longrightarrow m\mid(a+b)c\Longrightarrow \fbox{$ac+bc=mk$}\;\;\text{and}\\c+d\equiv0\pmod m\Longrightarrow m\mid c+d\Longrightarrow m\mid (c+d)b\Longrightarrow \fbox{$bc+bd=mj$}
ac+bc-bc-bd=mk-mj\\ac-bd=m(k-j)\\m\mid ac-bd\Longrightarrow ac\equiv bd\pmod m\;\;\;\;\;\;\Box
